==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Tinder
<hw>Tin"der</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[OE.
<ets>tinder</ets>, <ets>tunder</ets>, AS. <ets>tynder</ets>,
<ets>tyndre</ets>; akin to <ets>tendan</ets> to kindle, D.
<ets>tonder</ets> tinder, G. <ets>zunder</ets>, OHG. <ets>zuntara</ets>,
<ets>zuntra</ets>, Icel. <ets>tundr</ets>, Sw. <ets>tunder</ets>, Dan.
<ets>t⟦oum⟧nder</ets>. See <er>Tind</er>.]</ety> <def>Something very
inflammable, used for kindling fire from a spark, as scorched
linen.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><cs><col><b>German tinder</b></col>. <cd>Same as
<er>Amadou</er>.</cd> -- <col><b>Tinder box</b></col>, <cd>a box in
which tinder is kept.</cd></cs>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

